article.headline: Murray State 66, UC Davis 43
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. (AP) -- Darnell Hopkins scored 16 points and Murray State used its pressure defense to dominate UC Davis in a 66-43 win Tuesday night in the first round of the Shamrock Office Solutions Classic at Saint Mary's. Murray State (5-3) did not allow a field goal to any player for UC Davis (4-7) other than Fowzi Abdelsamad until 16:45 remained in the game. Abdelsamad had 15 of Davis' 16 first-half points but got only two shots in the second half when he was held scoreless. Abdelsamad was 4-for-7 in the first half, while the rest of his teammates went 0-for-11. Murray State never trailed as Hopkins hit a pair of 3-pointers for the first two baskets of the game. No one else on Murray State reached double figures, but 10 other players scored. The Racers were 9-for-17 on 3-point attempts and forced 19 turnovers. Its pressure prevented Davis from generating any offensive flow, forcing the Aggies to attempt many of their shots in the final five seconds of the 35-second shot clock. Murray State's biggest lead was 34 points at 62-28 before emptying its bench. Juston Stearns had 11 points for UC Davis, all in the second half. Murray State will face host Saint Mary's in in the tournament championship on Wednesday night. The Gaels beat Radford 72-60.
